The paper discusses the theoretical connections between Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) and Mean-Field Games (MFGs), which are both topics in machine learning and game theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
